Multi-talented actress, presenter and MC, Relebogile Mabotja, is expanding her brand and soaring to new heights in 2018.The popular personality has now joined the SABC 2 family as the executive producer of a new show, called Raising Babies 101.The weekly show debuted on Friday morning on SABC 2.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Relebogile is executive producing the show through her company which she owns with, partners Anthony Waymen-Nel and Nadia White.The company is called The TV Smiths.The show is presented by Carol Ofori in front of a studio-audience and is a talk series for first-time parents and caregivers in South Africa. “I’ve produced many television shows, but this is the first time that I am producing a show that I have been a part of from conception. It’s such a surreal feeling for it to have finally aired. I believe Raising Babies 101 is a pertinent show that South African parents and expectant parents will enjoy,” said Relebogile.